  "text": "Based on the above results, this shows that suspension cells can be transiently transfected with siRNA to a rather high efficiency and specificity, and that siRNA is a powerful tool to study nucleoside analog metabolism. It also shows that the decreased sensitivity is seen against nucleoside analogs and not to anthracyclines, as is seen when making cells nucleoside analog-resistant using nucleoside analogs in the cell medium during several months [CITATION_1] . We aim to use this technique further in the study of nucleoside analog resistance.",
